1
00:00:00,292 --> 00:00:01,667
He takes you through this path

2
00:00:02,250 --> 00:00:03,792
He grabs you at this place

3
00:00:03,792 --> 00:00:05,334
Then he takes you out through that door

4
00:00:06,375 --> 00:00:08,125
He brings you into the prison upstairs

5
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:12,417
Their prison was there, not here

6
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:23,626
Interviewer: When you came up from here, how many ISIS members were with you?

7
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:26,250
From here, one person took me

8
00:00:27,959 --> 00:00:31,792
He alone held my hand and led me from here to the other side

9
00:00:31,834 --> 00:00:33,417
Then to the other door and from there to the prison

10
00:00:34,876 --> 00:00:40,834
Interviewer: Do you remember if you saw anything
in front of you when you came up here now?

11
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,334
When I came up, I also saw people

12
00:00:45,375 --> 00:00:47,918
Other people besides me being brought inside

13
00:00:48,792 --> 00:00:52,918
They had brought civilians too, for reasons I didn’t know

14
00:00:53,209 --> 00:00:54,542
We were walking on our way

15
00:00:54,584 --> 00:00:57,959
Because when he took me out, he didn’t blindfold me the first time

16
00:00:58,542 --> 00:00:59,959
He took me straight there

17
00:01:00,709 --> 00:01:02,125
After he brought me into the prison

18
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:05,250
When he takes you out for interrogation

19
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:07,542
He blindfolds you and whips you

20
00:01:11,334 --> 00:01:18,542
Interviewer: Can you continue to tell us how the ISIS member took you to prison?

21
00:01:20,209 --> 00:01:22,667
When we went out the door, he held me here

22
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:26,918
Here he was holding me with his hand and I was walking behind him

23
00:01:28,375 --> 00:01:32,500
Until we reached the door

24
00:01:33,375 --> 00:01:38,250
One part of the door was open, not both sides

25
00:01:45,834 --> 00:01:47,918
Only one part of this door was open

26
00:01:48,709 --> 00:01:50,167
Both sides were not open

27
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:03,250
When we went out, the prison was behind us

28
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:10,959
Now it is destroyed, they blew it up

29
00:02:13,834 --> 00:02:19,500
Interviewer: Describe to me how you felt when they sentenced you

30
00:02:20,626 --> 00:02:22,292
It was six days, right?

31
00:02:22,417 --> 00:02:24,250
He didn’t sentence me to six days

32
00:02:25,751 --> 00:02:28,584
In their early days, you didn’t know your sentence

33
00:02:28,626 --> 00:02:30,542
They don’t sentence you for a month, for example

34
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:35,250
We were not in a military court of our state

35
00:02:35,709 --> 00:02:38,459
Meaning if you were guilty, they gave you a set sentence

36
00:02:38,959 --> 00:02:42,500
They didn’t have that here, they don’t give you two days, for example

37
00:02:42,584 --> 00:02:44,417
It’s unknown, it’s however long they want

38
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:48,334
Your stay or release is up to their will

39
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,584
Or they might bring you back again

40
00:02:51,667 --> 00:02:52,876
We lived like this

41
00:02:53,959 --> 00:02:57,667
Interviewer: How did you feel when you came out of the interrogation...

42
00:02:57,667 --> 00:03:00,250
and when the jailer took you to enter the prison cell?

43
00:03:02,292 --> 00:03:04,918
When he took me out from the interrogation

44
00:03:05,709 --> 00:03:07,000
And took me to prison

45
00:03:07,584 --> 00:03:10,417
I was anxious and afraid

46
00:03:12,542 --> 00:03:13,709
I was afraid

47
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:17,209
Because I was going into prison and didn’t know if I’d ever get out
